Martin du Pré Cooper  (17 January 1910 — 15 March 1986) was an English musicologist and author.
In 1950 he joined the Daily Telegraph as assistant to Richard Capell, succeeding him as chief music critic four years later when Capell died.
He remained at the Telegraph until his retirement in 1976 and was succeeded by Peter Stadlen.
He was also editor of the Musical Times between 1953 and 1956.
Cooper is best known for his book French Music, first published in 1951.
He married the artist Mary Stewart in 1940.
Cooper was appointed CBE in 1972.
